Integration Procedure Invocation from REST APIs

Use GET or POST calls to run an Integration Procedure and retrieve the result. A GET call can't include a JSON request body.

For an example, see Invoke a Chainable Integration Procedure with REST Calls.

NOTE: In REST notation, curly braces represent variables.

To get JSON data for an Integration Procedure, issue a GET call.
To post JSON data to an Integration Procedure, issue a POST call.
title: Invoking OmniStudio Integration Procedures from REST APIs
